## Scope

Implements RT (Jour de repos) and CT (Jour de compensation) as a **hard
constraint** that allocates rest days per resource per calendar month,
aligned with AZG (railway labor law) and BAR CCT (CFF collective
agreement):

- Min **4 RT** per calendar month
- Min **2 CT** per calendar month
- Min **6 combined** rest days per calendar month
- Rest interval = 24h measured from a prior-shift-end anchor (not
  midnight-bound)
- Cross-partition carryover of per-month counts and free weekends
- Coupling with LC-05 (free-weekend frequency) so a chosen free weekend
  counts toward the monthly rest quota

Replaces the abandoned post-processing approach
(`ct_rt_generator-27.03.md`) with a CP-SAT decision-variable model.

**Default behavior is unchanged.** LC-06 is gated by per-request flags
`rt_replannable` and `ct_replannable` which are False unless the trigger
payload explicitly includes `"RT Jour de repos"` and/or `"CT Jour de
compensation"` in `replannable_demand_type`. When both are False:

- `sanitize_replannable_types` behaves as before (RT/CT stay protected)
- LC-06 decision variables are not created
- LC-08 v2 remains the safety-net combined-rest check
- JSONB and `planner_assignments` rows all have
  `assignment_type='DEMAND'`
- `planner_output.fetch_rt = fetch_ct = TRUE` (FE reads RT/CT from the
  external DB as today)

