## Constraint architecture

```
Planning range:     [2026-04-15 ─────────────────────── 2026-06-10]
                           │                                      │
LC-06 (monthly blocks):   ┌┴────────┐ ┌─────────────┐ ┌──────────┴─┐
                          │Apr 15-30│ │May 1-31     │ │Jun 1-10    │
                          │(53%)    │ │(full month) │ │(33%)       │
                          │rt≥3,ct≥2│ │rt=4,ct=2    │ │rt≥2,ct≥1   │
                          │comb≥4   │ │comb=6       │ │comb≥2      │
                          └─────────┘ └─────────────┘ └────────────┘
LC-05 (5-week windows):
  Rolling, crosses month boundaries, unchanged by LC-06.

LC-04 (pairwise):         No window — demand-to-demand min 12h gap.

Coupling:
  LC-05 fw[r,w]=1 ⟹ LC-06: rt[r,Sat]+ct[r,Sat] ≥ 1
                           rt[r,Sun]+ct[r,Sun] ≥ 1
  Prior-partition free weekends in free_weekend_by_month force rt+ct ≥ 1
  on any Sat/Sun that falls inside the current planning range.
```

